We recommended that the:
a. Municipal officials and employees with cash advances liquidate their CAs within the prescribed period pursuant to Section 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;
b. Municipal Accountant (i) cause the withholding of salary of accountable officers who failed to liquidate their CAs within the prescribed period, and (ii) require all officials and employees to submit electronic copy of official receipts to support claims of taxi and van fare and to use the certification for expenses not requiring receipts for expenses incurred amounting to ₱300 or less.

We recommended that the:
a. Inventory Committee prepare RPCLRN in accordance with COA Circular No. 2015-008;
b. Municipal Engineer prepare a schedule of the Local Roads indicating therein the cost of each Road Network Component such as (a) road lot, (b) road pavement, (c) drainage and slope protection structures, (d) and other miscellaneous structures to be submitted to the GSO and Accounting Office. Moreover, subsequent road projects of the Municipality should clearly indicate the separate cost of each road component for easy reference. The Engineering Office is also vested to determine the life of the Local Roads taking into consideration the (1) design, (2) type of users, and (3) volume of users of the roads. Such detail should also be included in the schedule of Local Roads as basis for the depreciation of the Road Components to be applied by the Accounting Office;
c. Municipal Accountant prepare a subsidiary record for each component of the road network and Local Road Network Ledger Card; and
d. Municipal GSO prepare and maintain RLRN and LRNPC to account for the Local Roads.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor through the GFPS-TWG Chairperson:
a. Prioritize the attendance of the GFPS Executive Committee, TWG and MET to various GAD-related trainings and seminars in order for them to help accelerate the gender mainstreaming in the Municipality;
b. Coordinate with the MPDC for the updated data of CBMS that will be used in the maintenance of the GAD Database with sex-disaggregated data and other relevant data that will aid in identifying GAD-responsive PPAs which is either client-focused or organization-focused;
c. Comply with the provisions of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No. 2013-01 dated July 18, 2013, as amended by JMC No. 2016-01 dated January 12, 2016 and COA Circular No. 2014-001 dated March 18, 2014 relative the observance of timelines in the preparation and submission of GPB and GAR; and
d. Require the GAD-IAC to prepare the IRR of the CY 2012 GAD Code of the Municipality to effectively implement the provisions contained therein.
